===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|日|丁|c1=s|c2=p|ls=psc}}.

According to Shuowen Jiezi, the sun ({{lang|zh|日}}) appearing over the horizon ({{lang|zh|一}}). However, this version is not the original one and this interpretation belongs to folk etymology. This simplification is the same that appears in [[正]].

Unrelated to the top component of [[得]]. Also unrelated to [[查]].

===Etymology 1===
Cognate with {{cog|cdm|दारःदो|tr=darʔ.do|t=place of sunrise; in east}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Unrelated to {{och-l|丹|cinnabar; red}}.

